nternational summits such as the Conference on Sustainable Developmentin Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (Rio+20) to the European Parliament, which he was thefirst General Assembly President to address, to academic institutions fromOxford to Moscow to Morocco.Al-Nasserstructures the book as he did his 66th session, around four mainthemes or “pillars:” mediation, UN reform, natural disaster prevention andresponse, and sustainable development.He offers a wide range of recommendations to intergovernmentalinstitutions, to states, to the public sector, and to individuals. Al-Nasser was determined to leave behinda General Assembly that the people of the world could look up to and depend on.This volume is a testament to all that he accomplished in that regard, and aunique resource for those interested in knowing more about the world’s mostrepresentative body at a crucial moment in history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aConflict managementxInternational cooperation. 0aHuman securityxInternational cooperation. 0aInternational relationsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aNatural disastersxPreventionxInternational cooperation. 0aPacific settlement of international disputes. 0aSustainable developmentxInternational cooperation. 0aWorld politicsx2015-2015. 0aWorld politicsy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aKi-moon, Ban.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831107289960 cprintz978147986200940uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479862009.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479841851423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479841851/original  a978-3-11-072899-6  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL